<BaseLayout title="About - BeaconGuard">
	<h1>About</h1>

	<h2>The Audit Trail Gap</h2>

	<p>Healthcare AI systems operate in environments where authorization decisions must remain defensible for extended periods. Regulatory requirements demand audit trails that span years, not months.</p>

	<p>Traditional AI logging captures model inputs and outputs, but fails to preserve the authorization context that governed those decisions. As models evolve and prompts change, historical logs become semantically disconnected from their original governance intent.</p>

	<p>This creates an auditability gap: systems can demonstrate what happened, but cannot prove why authorization decisions were made according to the policies that existed at the time of execution.</p>

	<h2>Deterministic Governance Requirement</h2>

	<p>Healthcare governance requires deterministic replay of authorization logic. Policy evaluation must produce identical results when presented with identical inputs, regardless of when the evaluation occurs.</p>

	<p>The challenge emerges from the temporal nature of AI systems. Models drift, training data changes, and prompt engineering evolves. Authorization policies, however, must remain immutable and replayable.</p>

	<p>Without deterministic governance, healthcare organizations cannot provide the non-repudiation required for regulatory compliance and patient safety assurance.</p>
</BaseLayout>